   {
      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "ACK the first and third commits (_rpc: Expose g_is_mempool_loaded via getmempoolinfo and /rest/mempool/info.json_ and _Move g_is_mempool_loaded into CTxMemPool::m_is_loaded_). I like the tidy up in _Move g_is_mempool_loaded into CTxMemPool::m_is_loaded_ to remove the `g_is_mempool_loaded` global.\r\n\r\nI don't see the need for the second commit (_rpc: Set g_is_mempool_loaded early if the mempool is not persisted_). Having two places where `m_is_loaded_` gets set seems to add complexity for no good reason. I don't think any users will see any behaviour difference before and after that commit.",
